summary: Pokemon Card of the Day #1496: Energy Search (Black & White)
title: Pokemon Card of the Day #1496: Energy Search (Black & White)
body:
Energy Search was one of those cards that never really went away. It was almost a lock for reprints every year or two. The effect was really simple in that it was an Item card that had you search your deck for a basic Energy card and put it into your hand. You’d rather run an extra Energy over this most of the time, but things changed a bit in the BLW-On format.

In that format, Skyla existed. That was a Supporter that could search your deck for a Trainer of any kind to put into your hand. This suddenly brought on a bit of a niche for Energy Search in Darkrai EX decks, since a Skyla could be turned into a basic Darkness Energy if needed. Since Darkness Energy allowed a Pokemon to retreat for free when Darkrai EX was on the field, Energy Search provided an extra safe way out. It was still a bit lackluster outside of that deck and maybe those running a lot of different types of Energy for whatever reason, but it was about as good as Energy Search had ever been.
